# Localization (Compose Resources)

## Resource layout
- Localization resources live under `*/src/*/composeResources/values*/strings.xml`.
  - Example:
    - `core/common/src/commonMain/composeResources/values/strings.xml`
    - `core/common/src/commonMain/composeResources/values-ru/strings.xml`
- Use ISO language code in the folder name suffix:
  - `values-ru`, `values-en`, etc.
- Keep **one** `strings.xml` per locale folder (do not split files).

## Naming conventions
- Prefer stable, code-driven resource ids that match parsers:
  - common errors: `error_common_*`
  - user errors: `error_user_*`
  - security errors: `error_security_*`
- Avoid ad-hoc ids; new user-facing text introduced for an error should be added alongside the error parser mapping.

## Completeness
- When you add a new error code / UI string referenced from an `AppErrorParser`:
  - add translations in every existing locale folder in that module
  - keep the fallback behavior in `CommonErrorParser` for unknown codes
